An easy healthy dessert that satisfies your sweet tooth 😋🍎🍫

Instructions:

1 apple 
2 tablespoons pecans 
1/4 teaspoon ground cinnamon 
1 tablespoon semi sweet chocolate chips 

~275 calories 

Cut apple in small squares, add crushed pecans, add cinnamon. Melt chocolate chips in microwave for a few seconds and add to a ziplock bag in a corner. Cut corner and drizzle chocolate over everything. 😋

This is oatmeal recipe is so filling and so good! 😋 You can add different toppings to change your the flavor. 

Instructions:
1/2 cup water 
3/4 cup milk of choice 
1/2 cup old fashioned rolled oats 
1/8 teaspoon salt
1 tablespoons sweetener 
1 tablespoon chia seeds 
1/2 banana 

Bring water, milk, salt to a boil, lower the heat. Add oats, chia seeds, and sweetener of choice. Cook on low until oats have absorbed most of the liquid. Remove from heat and serve with sliced bananas 😋.

~350 calories

 It has sharp blades and cuts straight down and if you stick to one pass only per section I don’t see the loss of volume my losing 1/4 inch at the ends of your strands.

I was so embarrassed I felt like my accident wasn’t so bad and I should be better but the anxiety and irrational fears wouldn’t go away. I kept making content and carrying on quietly except in therapy.

The Inez Grant Parker Memorial Rose Garden is a beautiful and tranquil garden located in Balboa Park, San Diego, California. It is dedicated to the memory of Inez Grant Parker, a prominent community leader and advocate for the preservation of Balboa Park. 

The rose garden spans across two acres and features over 1,600 rose bushes, encompassing more than 130 varieties of roses. It is a popular destination for visitors, rose enthusiasts, and photographers seeking to capture the beauty of the flowers.

The garden is divided into several smaller themed sections, creating a diverse and captivating experience. These sections include the Shakespearean Garden, which features roses named after characters from the famous playwright’s works, and the Comstock Garden, which showcases roses that were popular during the Victorian era.

Visitors can stroll along the winding pathways, taking in the vibrant colors and fragrances of the roses. There are also benches strategically placed throughout the garden, allowing visitors to sit and relax while enjoying the picturesque surroundings.

The Inez Grant Parker Memorial Rose Garden is meticulously maintained by numerous volunteers and city staff, ensuring that the roses are always in peak condition. It is a designated All-American Rose Selections (AARS) Garden, meaning that it consistently showcases some of the best rose varieties in the country.

In addition to its natural beauty, the garden offers educational opportunities for visitors. There are interpretive displays throughout the garden that provide information on rose care, varieties, and their historical significance.

Overall, the Inez Grant Parker Memorial Rose Garden is a delightful retreat within Balboa Park. Whether you are a nature lover, a rose enthusiast, or simply seeking a peaceful setting, this garden offers a serene and aesthetically pleasing experience that is sure to captivate and inspire. #balboaparksandiego #rosegarden #inezgrantparkermemorialrosegarden #sandiegogems #exploresandiego #entrepreneurlifemotivation  #entrepreneurlifestlye  #longhairbeauty #emprendedoraslatinas #mexicanaenusa #hotsenoralife

✅1. Hygiene- Hair brushes collect dirt, oil, dead skin cells, and product residue over time. Regular cleaning helps remove these buildups, preventing them from transferring back onto your hair.

✅2. Maintaining Hair Health- Dirty brushes can transfer accumulated oils and dirt back onto your hair, making it look greasy and potentially causing scalp issues. Clean brushes help keep your hair clean and healthy.

✅3. Prolonging Brush Life- Regular cleaning prevents the accumulation of gunk that can damage the bristles or the brush base, increasing its longevity and effectiveness.
"
✅4. Preventing Bacterial Growth- A dirty brush can become a breeding ground for bacteria.

✅5. Better Styling Results- Clean brushes provide smoother styling. They can glide through the hair more easily without catching on residue or tangled hair strands.

How I wash mine: 👇

✅Fill sink with water 

✅Ass a detox shampoo 

✅Let them  sit a few minutes and scrub them gently with another brush to use the bristles to clean each other

✅Rinse

✅Lay flat to dry

✅ The secret to long hair is length retention. Scalp oiling is popular, but if the new growth isn’t properly cared for, the length won’t be retained. You can go without oiling your scalp and keep your haircare routine simple if you haven’t experienced hair fall. 

✅ If your ends are thinning but not from hair fall, you need to practice the 7-Daily Hair Habits to prevent this.

You’ll need some products to retain your length as healthy as possible:

✅ You need oils to protect your ends from mechanical damage and daily friction.

✅ A satin or silk pillowcase to reduce friction and wear

✅Eating a well-rounded diet to prevent slow hair growth or, in some cases, hair fall

✅ Scrunchies or claw clips instead of hair elastics

✅ Gentle shampoos for your hair porosity

✅ Weekly hair mask 

✅ Biweekly hair detox with a clarifying shampoo

✅Only trim your hemline (longest layer) as needed when it has visible damage 

✅ Use hair shears to do a monthly hair dusting to cut the damage and not your length ✨

#longhairtips #longhairjourney #haircaretips #longhairgoals #tipsdecabello #cabellolargo #healthyhairjourney

A few things that slowed me down in the long hair journey:

❌ Styled haircuts were my most significant setbacks because they always cost me inches of length when the layers weren’t even and the longest layer was too thin. 

✅ I eventually stuck to only getting face-framing layers in the front and 2-3  long layers in the back. I cut the last bit of layers I had in the back this week, and you can see how thick I left my hemline. 

✅ The thicker your hemline is, the more protected your ends are.

❌ Using titanium hair tools fried my hair. Even at a lower heat, it seemed to cause more damage. (more details in the book)

✅  I switched to ceramic heat tools with ion technology 

❌ Not oiling my ends daily for protection 

❌ Used sulfate-based shampoo every wash.

✅ Switched to a more gentle shampoo L’Oréal Ever Pure Glossing or the  Moisture one

❌ Didn’t do routine hair detoxes, and my hair would get dry even though I wasn’t processing or using a lot of heat and used hair masks.

✅ Started a biweekly hair detox

Simple but effective ways to protect your length: 

✅ sleep on silk or satin

✅reduce heat use

✅use a microfiber towel

✅oil your ends to protect them from friction and wear

✅don’t lift more than 3 shades of your natural hair color 

✅use bonding products if you have high porosity 

✅use lighter products for low & normal
porosity hair (if you don’t process your hair and don’t use heat but have dry hair do a hair detox ➡️ you probably have buildup and using bonding products adds to the problem)

When you take the proper haircare steps you don’t need expensive professional products for your hair to look good. ✨ I teach you in The Long Hair Handbook. Here’s some tips to get you started ⬇️

👉 Some professional products feel nicer but they’re not required for healthy and long hair. Most long haired women I know use inexpensive drugstore products. 

✅ Easy things you can do to get the best hair results:

✅ Use a detox shampoo like the Kristin Ess Clarifying shampoo biweekly and a hair mask after.

✅ Use a microfiber towel.

✅ Use a scalp scrub to remove buildup if your  clarifying shampoo doesn’t do enough for you.

✅ When blow drying, squeeze out excess water first then apply heat protectant. Use a lower heat in constant motion 15 inches away.

✅ Reduce use of direct heat from curling irons and straighteners. If you do use frequent heat invest in the better heat products with better technology like the Dyson Airstrait for pin straight hair or the Dyson AirWrap for a blowout look (with the thicker barrel). 

✅ Use a hair mask weekly.

✅ Oil your ends with an oil like the ones I’ve linked in my Amazon storefront. See IG highlights for the link. ❤️

If you’re new here I highly recommend you check out The Long Hair Handbook where I simplify everything you need to get started and achieve your hair goals faster. 🙌

Tangles are normal because of wind and friction throughout the day! Oiling your ends help with tangles and protect them.
